+# P4.14 — warning policy / notifier route binding
+
+## Goal
+
+Invalidate a dual-control silence approval when the operational class of the incident changes even if the core drift body remains broadly similar.
+
+## What is now bound
+
+- `warning_codes`
+- `warning_severity_policy`
+- `notifier_route_class`
+
+## Policy env
+
+- `LATENCY_CONTRACT_DEPLOY_LINT_NOTIFY_WARN_CODES_WARN_CSV`
+- `LATENCY_CONTRACT_DEPLOY_LINT_NOTIFY_WARN_CODES_CRIT_CSV`
+- `LATENCY_CONTRACT_DEPLOY_LINT_NOTIFY_WARN_CODES_PAGE_CSV`
+
+## Effects
+
+- `prepare-override` stores route-aware binding.
+- final `ack` invalidates approval if warning policy or notifier route class changed.
+- notifier emits `warning_severity_policy` and `notifier_route_class` in ops/notify payloads.
+
+## Key metrics
+
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_silence_approval_warning_policy_match`
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_silence_approval_notifier_route_class_match`
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_summary_dual_control_route_binding_mismatch_total`
